docs.abstract: The former editor of Cosmopolitan was one of the company’s top executives. But last week Troy Young became the new president of its magazine division.
docs.snippet: The former editor of Cosmopolitan was one of the company’s top executives. But last week Troy Young became the new president of its magazine division.
docs.lead_paragraph: On July 25, Hearst Magazines named Troy Young as its new president. And now the magazine company behind Esquire, Cosmopolitan and Harper’s Bazaar has lost its chief content officer.

headline.main: Joanna Coles Quits as Hearst’s Chief Content Officer
headline.print_headline: As a Leader Joins Hearst, Another One Is Departing

docs.abstract: The company’s pay changes are its latest move to fix a corporate culture that women said was rife with harassment and discrimination.
docs.snippet: The company’s pay changes are its latest move to fix a corporate culture that women said was rife with harassment and discrimination.
docs.lead_paragraph: More than 7,000 Nike employees will be getting raises after an internal pay review, undertaken after claims of workplace misconduct and discrimination against women, shook the company and forced out several of its top executives.

headline.main: Nike Will Raise Wages for Thousands After Outcry Over Inequality
headline.print_headline: After Outcry Over Treatment of Women, Nike Will Raise Wages for Thousands of Workers

docs.abstract: Regulators are clamping down on the credit bureau in the aftermath of the breach, which left 147 million people vulnerable.
docs.snippet: Regulators are clamping down on the credit bureau in the aftermath of the breach, which left 147 million people vulnerable.
docs.lead_paragraph: Equifax agreed to a number of data security rules under a consent order with eight state financial regulators that was announced on Wednesday, the latest regulatory response to the breach that allowed hackers to steal sensitive personal information on more than 147 million people.

headline.main: 8 States Impose New Rules on Equifax After Data Breach
headline.print_headline: 8 States Impose New Rules On Equifax for Data Breach

docs.abstract: The Fed’s chairman, Jerome H. Powell, said the central bank expected both inflation and unemployment to remain at historically low levels for some time.
docs.snippet: The Fed’s chairman, Jerome H. Powell, said the central bank expected both inflation and unemployment to remain at historically low levels for some time.
docs.lead_paragraph: BOSTON — Jerome H. Powell, the Federal Reserve chairman, said Tuesday that the American economy is enjoying an unusual but sustainable period of low unemployment and low inflation. He described the current moment, and the Fed’s expectation that it will continue, as “not too good to be true.”

headline.main: Fed’s Powell Says Strong Economic Path ‘Not Too Good to Be True’
headline.print_headline: Fed Chief Says Economy Is ‘Not Too Good to Be True’

docs.abstract: Ten years ago, the social network introduced a password system that connected it to a broad swath of the internet. Now we are seeing the downside.
docs.snippet: Ten years ago, the social network introduced a password system that connected it to a broad swath of the internet. Now we are seeing the downside.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — When Mark Zuckerberg introduced an online tool called Facebook Connect in 2008, he hailed it as a kind of digital passport to the rest of the internet. In just a few clicks, users would be able to log in to other apps and sites with their Facebook passwords.

headline.main: Facebook Hack Puts Thousands of Other Sites at Risk
headline.print_headline: Thousands of Sites at Risk After Facebook Is Hacked
